verses.text:
He that hath pity upon the poor lendeth  unto the \nd LORD\nd*;
and that which he hath given will he pay him again.\f + \fr 19.17 
\ft that which…: or, his deed\f*

Divers weights \add are\add* an abomination unto the \nd LORD\nd*;
and a false balance \add is\add* not good.\f + \fr 20.23  \ft a false…: Heb. balance of
deceit\f*

So shall thy poverty come \add as\add* one that travelleth;
and thy want as an armed man.\f + \fr 24.34  \ft an…: Heb. a man of
shield\f*
